# stringWidth micro-benchmark
# Context: rolldown@1.0.0-rc.15/rc.16 inlines string-width@7.x in dist/shared/rolldown-build-*.mjs
# stringWidthFull = exact port of rolldown inlined version
# stringWidthPatched = .length fast-path (what our local patch does)

N chunks | chars/line | full (ms) | patched (ms) | ratio | full per-line µs
---------|------------|-----------|--------------|-------|------------------
     100 |         89 |      0.95 |         0.03 |  28.1x |             9.5
     500 |         89 |      4.04 |         0.05 |  85.9x |             8.1
    1000 |         89 |      8.78 |         0.09 |  93.3x |             8.8
    2000 |         89 |     16.71 |         0.21 |  79.8x |             8.4
    5000 |         89 |     43.55 |         0.37 | 118.1x |             8.7
   10000 |         89 |     85.26 |         0.88 |  96.4x |             8.5

# Projection: if App emits 9,399 chunks and FancyReporter.formatLogObj
# calls stringWidth twice per line (left + right), total stringWidth calls = ~18,800.
# Scaled cost = (full_per_line_us * 18,800) / 1000 ms
